flowchart TD
  A[Trigger: Daily scheduled run (nightly planning window) plus event-driven triggers for expedited orders or capacity-impacting incidents (e.g., high-priority sales order, machine outage).]
  A --> N1[Stream: DDM/Crawlers - Ingest master, orders, inventory, and capacity data]
  N1 --> N2[Stream: STREAMS - Transform and validate scheduling dataset]
  N2 --> N3[Cortex: Remote Functions - Compute optimized line-level sequence and capacity allocation]
  N3 --> N4{PB: Process Builder (Process + Rules) - Apply business rules and exceptions, finalize plan}
  N4 -->|Primary| N5[PB: Remote Functions - Execute schedule and upstream/downstream write-backs]
  N5 --> N6[PB: UI Screen - Surface plan and exceptions to planners/operators]
  N6 --> Z1[Outcome: Lower COGS via reduced changeovers and optimized runs, improved on-time delivery, better capacity utilization, and reduced working capital through synchronized MRP and targeted expedites.]
  N4 -->|Solver identifies capacity shortfall ...| B1[Process Builder triggers supplier expedited flow via Remote Functions and opens CWB Lifecycle items for planner approval when cost/lead-time tradeoffs exceed thresholds]
  B1 --> O1[Outcome: Supplier expedite requested and routed for approval; if approved, supplier PO/ASN updates are executed; otherwise schedule flags for alternative recovery actions]
  O1 --> End[End]
  N4 -->|MES or ERP writeback fails or returns...| B2[Automated retry logic in Remote Functions with escalation: create notification and action item for plant operations and lock affected schedule segments]
  B2 --> O2[Outcome: Manual intervention scheduled; schedule segments held to prevent incorrect execution until resolved]
  O2 --> End[End]
  N4 -->|Excessive changeover cost or overtime...| B3[Process Builder evaluates cost trade-off rules and either reschedules lower-priority runs, applies overtime via Remote Functions, or surfaces CWB for executive approval]
  B3 --> O3[Outcome: Decision applied that balances cost vs. service level; resulting schedule either increases cost (overtime/expedites) or relaxes delivery targets for non-critical orders]
  O3 --> End[End]
  Z1 --> End[End]